				\begin{document}$$C_i^{3 - }$$\end{document} and CBr3−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{Br}^{3 - }$$\end{document} impurities are relatively low under n-type conditions, and they become the major impurities of carbon electrodes.Fig. 2Impurity formation energies.
The calculated formation energies of a carbon (two different carbon sources are considered: graphite (dashed line) or graphene (solid line)), and b metal (Au, Ag, and Cu) impurities as a function of the Fermi level, Ef, under the Sn-rich and Moderate conditions.

